cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is about semantic image segmentation using fully convolutional neural networks (FCNs) with an attention mechanism to weight multi-scale features. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel attention mechanism, which involves learning to weight features at each pixel location, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves training a deep neural network, which could also place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of extra supervision to achieve better performance, which could place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on three challenging datasets, which could also place it in cs.MM (Multimedia).
